cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CR 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision and deep learning techniques for human re-identification, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The use of deep Siamese CNN architectures also suggests that it may belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new gating function to selectively emphasize fine local patterns, which could fall under the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category. The use of neural networks for image comparison and feature extraction also suggests that it may belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with visual surveillance and security, which could fall under the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category.
